<H4>December 2009 </H4>With the Holiday Season in full swing, don’t miss out on these last minute reminders and updates for the 2010 International CES. We’ll see you Vegas in just a few short weeks. Have a safe and happy Holiday Season! <BR><BR>The 2010 Exhibitor PR Newsletter is distributed on the first Wednesday of every month to all CES Exhibitor PR Contacts. Please visit CESweb.org for past editions. <BR><BR>
<H3>Upcoming Deadlines CE Vision Magazine Ad Deadline – December 11</H3>Only one trade magazine gives you access to the top leaders at CES - <A href="http://ce.org/Press/CEA_Pubs/3501.asp" target=_blank>Consumer Electronics Vision</A>. One out of every three CE Vision readers has visited an advertiser’s booth at a show after seeing their ad in CE Vision.&nbsp; <A href="http://ce.org/Press/CEA_Pubs/3501.asp" target=_blank>CE Vision</A> ads drive booth traffic!<BR><BR>As the official magazine of the Consumer Electronics Association (CEA), the producer of the International CES, <A href="http://ce.org/Press/CEA_Pubs/3501.asp" target=_blank>CE Vision</A> gets exclusive distribution at key meeting places on the show floor. From exhibitor booths to member lounges to VIP buyers, CE Vision is there – with what’s hot at the show, the trends are for 2010 and key business development strategies. Take this unique opportunity with CE Vision to tell your story to critical industry influentials. Plus, CE Vision drives web traffic.&nbsp; More than one out of every two readers have sought out information about an advertiser’s product via the advertiser’s website after seeing their ad in CE Vision.&nbsp; Contact Dan Cole at 703-907-7987 for advertising opportunities. January/February issue: Space closes December 4, materials are due December 11.<BR><BR>
<H3>Press Kit preparation – ELECTRONIC ONLY</H3>This is your final reminder that this year the International CES press kit area is going green! In an effort to reduce our environmental footprint and in accordance with media feedback, the LVCC press room will only house electronic exhibitor press kits.&nbsp; Exhibitors are welcome to bring in a one page spec sheet in addition to an electronic format of choice; including USB, CDs or hosting online. Printed press materials greater than one page in length should be stored in the exhibitor’s booth. Recent CES surveys show that 85 percent of media prefer online, USB or CD-ROM kits with a one page spec sheet. Make sure your electronic press kit is marked clearly with the company's name and CES booth number for easy reference. We recommend that you bring between 250-500 electronic press kits to the CES Press Room. <BR><BR>
<H3>Press Kit Shipping Information</H3>Online press kits may be ordered through our <A href="/docs/OnlineMedia.pdf" target=_blank>Online Media Center</A> and set-up at any time prior to, during and even after the event. However, if you plan on shipping your electronic (USB and/or CD) press kits to the press room, please mark them to arrive between December 31, 2009 and January 4, 2010. Due to the volume of shipments arriving at the LVCC, all shipments arrive at the same distribution center and are then delivered accordingly, which usually takes 2‐3 days.<BR><BR>Press Kit Mailing Address<BR>Las Vegas Convention Center<BR>2010 International CES<BR>c/o GES Exposition Services<BR>Exhibitor Name<BR>Deliver To: PRESS ROOM, S229<BR>Las Vegas Convention Center<BR>3150 Paradise Rd.<BR>Las Vegas, NV 89109<BR>Phone: 703‐907‐7603<BR><A href="mailto:prcontacts@CE.org">prcontacts@CE.org</A> <BR><BR>
<H3>CES Unveiled</H3>Tuesday, January 5, 2009 <BR>Time is running out to <A href="http://www.cesweb.org/exhibitors/sponsorships/pressOpportunitites.asp#792">participate in CES Unveiled: The Official Press Event of the 2010 International CES</A>. Debut your company’s new products at this highly regarded press event to more than 900 top-tier media, as well as market and financial analysts. Don’t miss your chance to stand out above the crowd and network with high-level press just two days before the show. Contact Ryan Strowger at <A href="mailto:rstrowger@CE.org">rstrowger@CE.org</A> right away for information including tabletop and sponsorship opportunities. <BR><BR>
<H3>Tell Us About Your Celebrity Appearances and Special Events </H3>Monster Cable just announced that six-time Grammy Award winner John Legend will perform at the Monster Retailer Awards/Concert at the 2010 International CES! Is your company planning a special concert with a popular chart‐topper, too? How about an autograph session with a Hollywood actor or a product demonstration with a sports legend? <A href="/docs/SpEventCeleb_form.pdf" target=_blank>If so, let us know! </A><BR><BR>We can assist you with special security arrangements, staging requirements, catering requests or anything else you need to make your event a success. We’ll help you publicize it by including details on CESweb.org, in news releases and in the press room. Many exhibitors that host special events or celebrities choose not to announce their events until closer to the show and we will certainly accommodate embargoes as well. <BR><BR>
<H3>Dave Graveline</H3>Don't miss your chance to be a guest on <A href="http://www.graveline.com" target=_blank>“Into Tomorrow with Dave Graveline”</A> -- THE Consumer Electronics Radio Show!&nbsp; Dave and his team will once again be broadcasting from the upcoming CES as they launch their 15th Season covering the latest in CE products -- including producing their national show from the 2010 International CES from January 7-10.&nbsp; If you will be introducing new and exciting consumer electronics products or services and would like to be considered as a guest, contact Dave’s Producer, Rob Almanza at <A href="mailto:rob@graveline.com">rob@graveline.com</A>.&nbsp; <BR><BR>
<H3>Follow Me</H3><STRONG>Reach Your Audience with the New CES Mobile App</STRONG><BR>Exhibitor information goes mobile with Follow Me! Follow Me is the first of its kind interactive Smartphone application designed specifically for tradeshows. It is a great tool that attendees can use to help navigate the show floor and discover what exhibitors they would like to visit. It is also a great way to reach the audience you want at your booth and delivers the only interactive advertisement of its kind. <A href="/docs/Follow_Me_rAdInfoSheet.pdf" target=_blank>Learn how you can increase your brand exposure with this new exciting tool. </A><BR><BR>
<H3>Link to CESweb for News Like Our 30 Days of Innovation Campaign</H3>Every business day leading up to the show, CNET is highlighting&nbsp; one of the record number of new 2010 CES exhibitors as part of our <A href="http://CESweb.org/30days">30 Days of Innovation</A> promotion. Make sure you check CESweb.org regularly for show updates and news in the month leading up to the 2010 International CES. <BR><BR>
<H3>CNET Best of CES Info</H3><STRONG>Finalists announced:&nbsp; 10 a.m. Friday, January 8<BR>Award show: 11 a.m. Saturday, January 9<BR>LVCC, South Hall 3 Lobby, CNET Stage<BR></STRONG><BR>CNET's expert editors will hit the deck running at the 2010 International CES to find the best, new products.&nbsp; They’ll comb through thousands of devices to find the most innovative gadgets that will set the standard by which they will measure all other products in the coming year. In the end, they will nominate 27 products across nine categories, plus a “Best in Show” winner. Also, from the top 27 products, the CNET audience watching online will award a “People’s Voice” winner. Don’t miss the live award show on Saturday at the CNET Stage. <BR><BR><STRONG>Past Issues:<BR><A href="/news/110409.asp">November 2009</A><BR><A href="/news/100709.asp">October 2009</A><BR><A href="/news/090209.asp">September 2009</A><BR><A href="/news/080509.asp">August 2009</A></STRONG>

    
                        
